abstract: The New York Times asked readers on Facebook who live in Ireland how the referendum is being discussed in their family.
snippet: The New York Times asked readers on Facebook who live in Ireland how the referendum is being discussed in their family.
lead_paragraph: One person described a vicious fight around the family dining room table. Another said her sister, mother and elderly grandmother were all on the same page. A third said his children couldnâ€™t understand why anyone would vote no.

lead_paragraph: Cameron Clarke Delany and Patrick Charles Pfeiffer were married Saturday at the home of the groomâ€™s parents in Pacific Palisades, Calif. The officiant was Daniel Madigan, a friend of the couple who became a minister with the American Marriage Ministries for the event.
